<TEXT>
a strong earthquake shook costa rica 
late thursday breaking windows in houses in southern cities near 
the border with panama a fire department official said 
there were no immediate reports of injuries 
firefighters in the panamanian city of david said the tremor was 
felt strongly in panamas western provinces of chiriqui and boca 
del toro both bordering costa rica but there were no reports of 
damage or injuries there either 
the temblor was not felt in panama city 
the quake registered 56 on the richter scale said an official 
in the communications office of san joses fire department he 
refused to be further identified 
no one answered telephones at the seismology institute 
the red cross said no damage was reported in san jose the 
capital 
the fire department official said the quake occured at 945 pm 
1045 pm est and was centered near buenos aires 70 miles 
southeast of san jose and 26 miles from the border with panama 
we have reports that the glass windows of many homes broke in 
the towns of buenos aires ciudad neily and san isidro and we 
are expecting possible reports of damage in puerto jimenez near 
buenos aires the official said 
san isidro is 48 miles southeast of san jose and ciudad neily is 
seven miles from the panamanian border 
he said the quake also was felt strongly in the city of golfito 
also near the border but communications were poor and there was no 
word of damage he said 
the people ran into the streets terrified in the cities of 
buenos aires and ciudad neily since the temblor was really 
strong johnny zamora of the red cross in san jose said 
in san jose tall buildings swayed 
definitely the quake was felt practically in all the 
country the fire department official said 
the richter scale is a measure of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number indicates an increase of 
10 times in ground motion 
an earthquake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage one 
measuring 6 can cause severe damage while a reading of 8 indicates 
a quake capable of tremendous damage 
</TEXT>
