<TEXT>
austria today marked the 50th anniversary 
of its annexation by nazi germany capping a bitter twoyear debate 
about its world war ii past that has polarized politics at home and 
tarnished its image abroad 
about 60 protesters gathered outside the chancellery to demand 
the resignation of president kurt waldheim members of the liberal 
greens party boycotted a special parliamentary session marking the 
annexation known as the anschluss 
during world war ii waldheim served as a lieutenant in a german 
army unit in the balkans that has been linked to nazi atrocities 
he has denied any wrongdoing 
fewer than 100 people turned out in a light rain as waldheim and 
other political leaders laid wreaths in separate ceremonies at 
monuments honoring austrias unknown soldiers and victims of 
fascism 
during the ceremonies a dozen protesters gathered outside the 
chancellory building 500 yards away carrying a banner that asked 
who will make waldheim resign 
until two years ago waldheim had not admitted that he served in 
the balkans unit since then he has resisted mounting pressure to 
resign 
greens delegates handed out pamphlets saying they were 
protesting waldheims presence at the hourlong session the 
pamphlets said waldheim is not representative of the austria that 
we want to commemorate 
the greens said they would instead travel to mauthausen site of 
a former nazi concentration camp near the city of linz to honor 
the victims of nazi germany 
chancellor franz vranitzky told a special cabinet session that 
the events of 1938 when this alpine nation was forcibly annexed to 
adolf hitlers third reich were a central theme of austrian 
politics today 
the events of 50 years ago pose relevant fundamental 
questions about the essence of politics vranitzky said if one 
attempts to avoid them they sooner or later return with greater 
emphasis 
vranitzky said austrians must recognize that crimes were 
committed by their countrymen during world war ii 
we must recognize the fact of historical guilt because as 
politicians we must draw lessons from the past failures of 
society he said 
vranitzky did not mention the waldheim controversy 
waldheim originally to speak at a hofburg palace ceremony was 
to remain out of the spotlight throughout the day 
instead waldheim commemorated the annexation with a nationally 
televised speech thursday in which for the first time he apologized 
