<TEXT>
a minor earthquake shook an area about 10 miles 
southeast of tacoma today but apparently did no damage officials 
said 
the temblor was recorded at 201 am pst according to the us 
geological surveys national earthquake information center in 
golden colo it measured 35 on the richter scale said the 
centers bruce presgrave 
there were no reports of damage or injury 
for a quake this size i really would not expect any 
presgrave said 
residents of fife federal way tacoma and auburn called local 
radio stations to report the quake 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
6 severe damage a 7 reading is a major earthquake capable of 
widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable of 
tremendous damage 
</TEXT>
