a powerful latewinter blizzard lashed the western plains with 
up to two feet of snow today closing hundreds of miles of highway 
in nebraska wyoming colorado and the dakotas and stranding 
hundreds of travelers 
up to 33 inches fell in the mountains of utah 
in southwestern nebraska the snow pileup cut off the town of 
kimball whose residents opened their doors to about 600 stranded 
motorists and in an adjacent section of colorado several hundred 
students had to spend the night in their school 
the storm occurred 100 years to the day after the start of the 
fourday great blizzard of 1888 in the eastern united states that 
storm claimed 400 lives 
the storm stalled near the nebraskawyoming line before moving 
east pumped heavy snow and winds gusting up to 40 mph from the 
western dakotas across western nebraska and much of wyoming and 
colorado 
in nebraska the storm was not expected to abate until late 
