favorable weather and by the time he decided to move secondplace 
herbie nayokpuk decided his team was rested enough to push on 
nayokpuk known as the shishmaref cannonball had arrived in 
cripple more than six hours behind redington but he left at 320 
pm only five minutes after the leader 
in third place was martin buser of big lake who pulled into 
cripple at 250 pm he was followed by fourtime iditarod champion 
rick swenson of two rivers at 320 pm joe garnie of teller at 
322 pm and defending champion susan butcher of manley at 435 
pm 
redington who arrived in cripple 525 miles from the start at 
450 am tried leaving at 9 am thursday but the sunsoftened 
snow turned him around 
no use to fight that let it harden up a little bit he said 
just before leaving thursday afternoon the dogs were right up to 
their bellies going along about 4 to 5 miles an hour i went out 
about three miles and came back thought id wait a while 
the delay gave an advantage to teams that have been hounding 
redington since he took the lead 260 miles back in rohn but he 
said there was little choice given the soft trail 
it doesnt hurt to give the dogs a little more rest he said 
from cripple the trail heads to ruby on the yukon river then 
follows the frozen river to kaltag and cuts over to unalakleet on 
the bering sea coast 
the first musher to reach nome will win 30000 the next 19 
finishers will split the rest of a 150000 purse 
two teams have dropped out of the race and two of the more than 
800 dogs running have died race officials said both deaths were 
ruled accidental 
