23 percent in february while sales at furniture and appliance 
stores were up a more modest 03 percent 
sales at specialty clothing stores climbed 06 percent in 
february only a partial rebound following a giant 33 percent 
january decline 
sales at gasoline stations fell 16 percent in february while 
sales at restaurants edged up 01 percent and sales at drug stores 
posted a 06 percent increase 
sales at grocery stores enjoyed a 07 percent rise in sales in 
february reversing a 06 percent january decline 
