<TEXT>
alpine skiers who seek out daring runs 
on unmarked trails accounted for half of all swiss avalanche deaths 
last winter and also pose problems for the environment officials 
said friday 
maj hugh lindsay a close friend of britains prince charles 
was killed thursday by a snowslide while skiing outside the normal 
slopes above klosters switzerland the traditional royal winter 
resort 
the heir to the british throne escaped unhurt 
the swiss federal avalanche research institute had warned 
thursday of considerable avalanche danger above 5250 feet in the 
region the party was skiing at about 5900 feet 
one obviously doesnt like seeing anyone getting killed but 
when you ski off the path that is your own responsibility said 
david bramwell a british skier vacationing in this remote village 
90 miles southeast of zurich 
