make offtrail skiers aware of safe areas to practice the sport 
the basic capital for tourism is unblemished nature said 
peter anrig of the swiss tourism association 
inexperienced skiers are known to rip through saplings 
ultimately killing off a future tree in a country concerned about 
widespread forest damage from pollution he said snow tourists 
also tend to litter in the otherwise virgin areas 
alpine animals are jolted by offtrailers experts say citing 
the example of the snow grouse skiers often scare the birds out of 
snow caves in which they hibernate leaving them to die of cold and 
consumption in glacial temperatures 
swiss avalanches have killed an average of 27 people each year 
over the past 50 years according to the federal institute six out 
of 10 victims are skiers 
lindsays death brought this winters toll to 12 
