thousands of workers across norway left 
their jobs for several hours friday to protest a government 
proposal to limit wage increases 
the labor government introduced the wage limitations in 
parliament friday and prime minister gro harlem brundtland 
condemned the protests as illegal 
the bill would limit the average workers increase on a weekly 
paycheck to 35 percent the government argued the move is needed 
to make norwegian products more competitive and curb last years 
87 percent inflation rate more than twice the european average 
the bill represents the most severe economic package since a 
15month wageprice freeze was approved 10 years ago it would 
limit pay raises to 15 cents an hour in the next two years 
bus drivers municipal employees nurses and thousands more 
workers in oslo and 10 other cities left their jobs norwegian 
radio went off the air for two hours 
about 1000 people demonstrated against the bill outside 
parliament in oslo we do not accept being robbed of our right to 
negotiate said jan andersengott spokesman for a whitecollar 
trade union federation 
six trade federations representing about 400000 workers were 
involved in the protests the norwegian news agency ntb reported 
the proposed law followed the lines of an agreement reached two 
weeks ago between employers and norways largest trade union 
federation which represents about 350000 members 
the legislation would take immediate effect upon passage which 
could be within a week 
