us district court jurors who may sit through six weeks of 
testimony listened to detailed descriptions of alleged fraud that 
involved millions of dollars and stretched from the oil fields of 
oklahoma to continentals offices in chicago 
the government has accused former continental vice president 
john lytle of buying highrisk loans from nowdefunct penn square 
bank in oklahoma city in exchange for nearly 600000 in kickbacks 
