<TEXT>
outgoing president antonio ortiz mena of the 
interamerican development bank predicted on friday that its loans 
to latin america will increase from last years 2361 billion to 
between 25 billion and 3 billion in 1988 
we can continue on this level until the end of the century 
ortiz mena told a news conference 
the bank owned by 44 governments is a major source of loans to 
raise the living standards of latin american countries most of 
which have seen declines in recent years from their already low 
levels 
after 17 years with the bank ortiz mena is returning to his 
native mexico he will be succeeded by enrique iglesias of uruguay 
ortiz mena blamed the drop in the banks lending in part on the 
drop in the value of the us dollar which he said cost the bank 
12 billion last year and will cost it another 2 billion in 1988 
the bank is deep in a dispute with the us government its 
biggest shareholder which is seeking more control over its lending 
ortiz mena denied that he had blocked a us effort to place a 
new man as the banks executive vice president james w conrow 
deputy assistant secretary of the treasury for developing nations 
he said the report was a fabrication 
ortiz mena will not be going to a meeting of the banks board of 
governors to be held in caracas venezuela on march 21 he said 
there would be discussion there of additional resources for the 
bank from japan he would not give a figure 
he added that there would also be discussion of increasing 
japans voting strength in the fund now 108 percent of the total 
the united states the largest contributor controls 345 percent 
of the votes 
ortiz mena said the major challenge for the interamerican bank 
is to help reverse the present situation in which capital is 
flowing out of latin america instead of into it the outflow much 
of it interest on old debts is estimated at 157 billion for 1987 
latin american countries can not fulfill theur debt 
commitments unless there is economic growth ortiz mena said 
to achieve growth it needs investment there can be no 
investment if it is exporting capital it needs to import capital 
