said then he leaped into his tractortrailer and drove for an hour 
at speeds of up to 90 mph with police pursuing 
on the freeway he jackknifed the empty truck apparently on 
purpose mallory said police closed the freeway in both 
directions stone sat in the vehicle with lots of ammunition 
said mallory 
police talked with stone first by cb radio and then via a 
militarystyle field telephone tossed into the cab he was 
distraught and felt as though his marriage was on the rocks he no 
longer wanted to live said tatum 
stone gave up after five hours firing a final blast out the 
truck window he suffered minor powder burns but was otherwise 
unhurt 
in 1978 in vacaville stone held off police with a gun in a 
domestic dispute tatum said no shots were fired and no one was 
injured according to police who had no further details relatives 
said he spent some time in jail as a result 
