<TEXT>
the texas hill country seemed an odd 
backdrop to talk with a man who ruled louisiana much like a king 
when he wasnt rolling dice in monte carlo and las vegas flirting 
with beautiful women or fighting off racketeering charges 
but gov edwin edwards is preparing to leave office monday and 
his texas ranch has been a hideaway used more frequently by the 
governor who became the most propular official in the bayou state 
since huey long until he was undone by the collapse of oil and 
questions about his honesty that wouldnt go away 
in a recent interview at the ranch overlooking the greenish 
waters of the south llano river edwards spoke softly about his 
political career and about leaving it all behind 
the 1400acre ranch is dotted with scrub oaks stunted by the 
scant rainfall a far cry from edwards louisiana estate with its 
massive mosscovered oaks and enough green grass in the yard to 
more than feed the 60 head of cattle barely surviving on what they 
can find here 
still the texas spread is far from the swirl of politics and 
controversy that has been his life 
edwards brother once said hes an introvert trying to be an 
extrovert 
thats accurate said edwards gently rocking and fiddling 
with the bottom button of a down jacket its almost ludicrous to 
say that but ive done a good job in overcoming it i have a basic 
tendency to get away thats why i have this ranch 
the ranch is not so much a place to relax for edwards who at 
60 still doesnt know how to take it easy 
if hes not hunting hes on that tractor or using a 
bushhog an aide told a reporter 
the reporter recalled a comment years ago by edwards 
brotherinlaw hes not relaxed like a normal frenchman 
maybe thats because hes ambitious said edwards 
motherinlaw 
edwards sprouted from impoverished south louisiana the son of a 
sharecropper education was the only escape route 
at 21 he had finished law school and six years later in 1954 
he was elected to the crowley city council from there he was 
elected to the state senate to congress and finally to the 
governors office in 1972 and again in 1976 
he never lost an election 
he was adored by the people because he brought les bons 
temps good times by prodding the legislature to tax oil at a 
percentage of value in 1973 just before prices soared government 
was on easy street and the economy was beautiful 
people were tolerant even proud of his candor when edwards 
commented that gambling turns me on they smiled when he 
flirted openly with women 
he left office after serving two consecutive terms the most 
allowed by law but returned in 1984 for an unprecedented third 
term overwhelming oneterm republican dave treen 
edwards was so powerful that while the republican served the 
populist cajun opened an unofficial governors office and began 
collecting 13 million for a campaign that kept treen looking over 
his shoulder 
edwards won with nearly 63 percent of the vote despite 
unfavorable publicity during his first two terms 
he had acknowledged receiving 20000 from a south korean 
whose dealings with congressmen and others led to the koreagate 
investigations 
he had shrugged off a book written by a former aide who 
accused edwards of selling state jobs and conquering legions of 
women 
he was investigated by the internal revenue service after all 
of the publicity about his gambling 
he was investigated during the fbi brilab probe that led 
to the conviction of a top aide 
edwards survived it all 
but in these last four years the king was felled by the 
collapse of oil prices which devastated the states economy and 
continued attacks on his honesty 
louisiana has one of the highest unemployment rates in the 
nation and the government is nearly bankrupt 
his answer to economic woes this term was a lottery and casino 
gambling something lawmakers would not buy edwards lost control 
of the legislature partly because of his two federal racketeering 
trials 
he went on trial in 1985 accused of brokering hospital permits 
obtained while in and out of office the jury was hung with all but 
two voting for acquittal 
in 1986 a second jury acquitted edwards and all other 
codefendants including his brother marion and several friends 
and aides 
i was shunned by the legislature during and between trials 
edwards said planting his boots on the ground to stop the rocking 
chair they saw how us attorney john volz used the federal 
grand juries they were scared if they can do that to you i 
dont want to be close to you there was an aura of fear in 
louisiana if volz and the other republicans could do that to me 
what could they do to legislators that was the feeling 
the polls showed that the people went along with the lottery 
idea and feeling the masses were still behind him edwards tried 
last year for a fourth term 
as a 44yearold congressman he had first swept into the 
governors office on a reform platform at age 60 he was beaten by 
buddy roemer a 44yearold congressman who used a reform platform 
complaining that edwards had given louisiana a banana republic 
image 
theres always been a mania to knock the man from the top of 
the mountain said edwards but it took them a lot of years 
its been a costly journey to the top 
in the last four years its been even worse my family has 
suffered my net worth has gone down considerably ive paid an 
awesome price onslaughts on my integrity from unfair 
investigations indictments but i think ive faced it 
realistically and altruistically 
in a 1979 interview edwards was reminded that he said that what 
he would like more than anything else is to convince people im 
honest 
i guess that is more what i would like to do now than ever 
but it seems like it is something that is going to escape me he 
said 
but i remind the people that despite all of the money spent 
all of the efforts made by people over the years theyve yet to 
prove anything 
whats going to happen now can edwards relax 
for about four days he said grinning i guess the phones 
will continue ringing people will still come to see me i feel 
nothing is going to happen with a new administration if thats 
true i will be sought out if not ill try to accept that 
in the meantime edwards will practice law with one of his sons 
and offer himself to the nations universities as a lecturer for 
5000 per appearance hell talk about legalized gambling and his 
career 
hell also hunt gamble and yes flirt 
i dont believe ive mellowed with age he said 
