<TEXT>
former merchant banker lord patrick spens was 
freed on 920000 bail raised by two friends after appearing in 
court friday to hear charges related to the guinness financial 
scandal 
spens a former managing director of merchant bankers henry 
ansbacher and co ltd was arrested and charged thursday for his 
alleged role in one of britains largest financial scandals 
he was ordered to appear in court again april 12 along with four 
others charged so far in the affair surrender his passport to 
police and not to contact employees from the ansbacher group 
two business friends alan lewis the chairman of a textiles 
company and charles longbottom former chairman of an ansbacher 
subsidiary paid spens bail the british domestic news agency 
press association reported 
police are investigating guinness tactics during its 4 billion 
1986 takeover of distillers co plc a scotch whisky and gin maker 
in what was then britains biggest acquisition ever 
spens 45 resigned from henry ansbacher in january 1987 under 
pressure from the bank of england and told reporters his alleged 
role in the guinness affair was perceived as an error of judgment 
he was subsequently charged in two counts with involvement in 
the improper payment of an interestfree loan of 14 million from 
guinness to ansbachers to fund the buying of more than 2 million 
shares in the brewing giant 
two other counts allege falsification of a document for 
ansbachers and conspiracy to create a false or misleading 
impression of the market value of guinness shares 
guinness has admitted arranging the allegedly illegal repurchase 
of its stock in an apparent effort to boost the price and make its 
cash and stock offer for distillers more attractive than a rival 
bid from argyll group plc a supermarket operator 
 
</TEXT>
