on the new york cotton exchange but fundamental factors also 
played a role in the rally said ernest simon cotton specialist in 
new york for prudentialbache securities inc 
from a fundamental point of view the futures market is the 
cheapest market around for us cotton simon said 
with futures priced three to five cents below cash cotton users 
who do not need supplies immediately can buy cotton at a bargain on 
the futures market 
