<TEXT>
the general services administration on friday 
extended by one month the deadline for bids on a new multibillion 
dollar government telephone system to give us sprint communications 
co more time to draft its proposal 
the gsa said it was reluctantly extending the deadline to 
april 29 but said it was doing so to insure the fullest possible 
competition for the contract one of the biggest ever let by the 
government 
besides sprint only two other teams of companies are bidding on 
the project the work for which will be split 6040 between two 
vendors 
the other bidders are a team led by american telephone amp 
telegraph co and another headed by martin marietta corp with mci 
communications corp 
us sprint a joint venture of gte corp and united 
telecommunications inc will team with gte government systems 
according to industry sources who spoke on condition they not be 
identified by name 
the contract for the new telecommunications system called 
fts2000 is valued at as much as 25 billion over 10 years the 
winners will replace the governments 25yearold phone system with 
a stateoftheart network for voice data video conferencing and 
other communications services 
the extension is the fifth time the bid deadline has been 
postponed since the contract was opened to bidding in january 1987 
last fall under pressure from congress the gsa revised the 
contract to split the award between two vendors instead of giving 
it all to one bidder 
us sprint originally had teamed with electronic data systems to 
bid on the project but they withdrew citing confusion in the 
procurement process however after the contract was revised us 
sprint decided to reenter the bidding 
us sprint officials declined to comment on the companys request 
for the extension but the gsa said us sprint needed the additional 
time to address many functions and aspects of the procurement 
they had previously assigned to eds in the original joint venture 
gsa administrator terence c golden said the agency determined 
that us sprint is indeed committed to competing for fts2000 and 
has in place the necessary resources to live up to its commitment 
to submit a proposal by april 29 
